consent: I consent to participate in this study. Take me to the study.
dgComp: You would earn $0.25, and the other person would earn $0.75
manipCheckPre:
I was told that this person doesn't have regular access to food, and that they also get some of their meals at a local soup kitchen. 

I was also told that neither of us will ever know each other's identity.
explanation:
First, I believe in fairness, so I'd like both of us to receive equal amounts. I also considered this unknown person's situation. 

However, my own situation is not far different. I've been getting SNAP food benefits for several years, but they were cut WAY back in March, and I now get only $35 a month - in the middle of inflation, including the cost of my rent and various grocery items themselves. I KNOW what it's like to go to bed and wake up hungry, and if this other person is real, I empathize with them. However, I also need the money I earn from Prolific to help pay my bills, and buy some food for myself, now that my SNAP benefits have been so drastically cut. The calculations used DON'T take into account inflation of food prices, nor realistic deductions for rent.

So this is why I decided to split the $1.00 equally between us.
manipCheckPost:
